data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span` of native-sized integers.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

The test confirmed reading/writing to both spans works correctly, with `nint` being 8 bytes on this 64-bit system. Note that `AllowUnsafeBlocks` must be enabled since `stackalloc` requires it.
